Package: scConvert
Type: Package
Title: Universal Single-Cell Format Conversion for R
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-03-10
Authors@R: c(
  person(given = 'Ziyu', family = 'Zeng', email = 'zzeng4@nd.edu', role = c('aut', 'cre', 'cph'), comment = c(ORCID = '0009-0005-4055-8492'))
  )
Description: Universal converter between single-cell data formats in R. Converts
  between any pair of h5Seurat, h5ad (AnnData), h5mu (MuData), Loom, Zarr, RDS,
  and SingleCellExperiment formats through a hub architecture using Seurat as an
  intermediate. Features memory-efficient direct HDF5 paths for h5ad/h5Seurat
  conversions, Visium spatial data roundtripping with image reconstruction,
  multimodal MuData support, and full Seurat v5 Assay5 compatibility. No Python
  or reticulate dependency required. Originally derived from SeuratDisk with
  substantial extensions for universal format coverage.
